    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe cursor is not redrawn properly after statuscolumn updates. The actual cursor position in `ruler` and `cursorcolumn` are correct.\r\n\r\n`;` in the video is actually `o`\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/23123008/ab3b42ea-527a-4ecd-b7cd-c7580778bd0d\r\n\r\nIssue in the plugin repo: https://github.com/luukvbaal/statuscol.nvim/issues/77\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean -u repro.lua repro.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\nfor name, url in pairs({\r\n\t\"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",\r\n\t\"https://github.com/luukvbaal/statuscol.nvim\",\r\n}) do\r\n\tlocal install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify(\"nvim_issue/\" .. name, \":p\")\r\n\tif vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\r\n\t\tvim.fn.system({ \"git\", \"clone\", \"--depth=1\", url, install_path })\r\n\tend\r\n\tvim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme(\"habamax\")\r\n\r\nlocal lspconfig = require(\"lspconfig\")\r\nlspconfig.lua_ls.setup({})\r\n\r\nlocal builtin = require(\"statuscol.builtin\")\r\n\r\nvim.opt.number = true\r\n\r\nrequire(\"statuscol\").setup({\r\n\tsegments = {\r\n\t\t{\r\n\t\t\tsign = {\r\n\t\t\t\tname = { \"Diagnostic\" },\r\n\t\t\t\tminwidth = 1,\r\n\t\t\t\tmaxwidth = 1,\r\n\t\t\t\tauto = true,\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t\t{ text = { builtin.lnumfunc }, click = \"v:lua.ScLa\" },\r\n\t\t{ text = { \" \" } }, -- This is necessary to reproduce, seems like this depends on statuscolumn width?\r\n\t},\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Make sure the `lua_ls` server is displaying signs\r\n2. Go to the end of the line where `statuscol` is require'd\r\n3. Press `o`\r\n4. The signs should disappear and the cursor should be offset by one column\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe cursor should be at the correct column\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-798+g72e619ca92\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.29.2, also tested in uxterm\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nneovim-git from chaotic-aur",
